# Vitals HQ — Support

Welcome to Vitals HQ support. Below you'll find answers to common questions, troubleshooting steps, and ways to reach us.

---

## Getting Started

**What is Vitals HQ?**
Vitals HQ is a life planner and health tracker for individuals and families. It brings medications, wellness check-ins, appointments, contacts, school info, and work details into a single private app.

**How do I set up my profile?**
When you first open Vitals HQ, you'll be guided through creating your profile with your name, date of birth, and basic health info. You can update any of this later in Settings → Manage Profiles.

**How do I add family members?**
Go to the Family tab and tap the "+" button. You can add a spouse, children, parents, or dependents. Each person gets their own profile with health tracking, contacts, and events tailored to their life stage.

---

## Subscriptions & Plans

**What's included in the free plan?**
The free plan supports a single profile with full access to medication tracking, wellness logs, events, contacts, and Siri Shortcuts.

**What do the paid plans include?**

- **Single** — One profile with premium features.
- **Couple** — Two profiles with full cross-member management.
- **Family** — Up to eight profiles with everything included.

**What happens if I downgrade?**
Your data is never deleted. Profiles beyond your new plan's limit become read-only — you can still view them, and medication reminders continue to fire. Upgrade again at any time to restore full access.

**How do I manage my subscription?**
Go to Settings → Subscription, or manage it through your Apple ID in the Settings app on your device under Subscriptions.

